# Smart Street Light System

## Objective

To design an energy-efficient smart street lighting system that automatically adjusts brightness based on ambient light conditions and human/vehicle movement.

## Problem Statement

Traditional street lights remain fully ON throughout the night, leading to unnecessary power consumption during periods of low activity.

This project addresses this issue by using an LDR to detect day/night conditions and a PIR sensor to detect motion, thereby adjusting light intensity dynamically.

## Components Used

* Arduino UNO
* LDR (Light Dependent Resistor)
* PIR Motion Sensor
* LED
* 10kΩ Resistor
* 220Ω Resistor
* Breadboard
* Jumper Wires

## Connections

### LDR Circuit

| Component      | Connection           |
| -------------- | -------------------- |
| LDR Terminal 1 | 5V                   |
| LDR Terminal 2 | A0 and 10kΩ resistor |
| 10kΩ resistor  | GND                  |

### PIR Sensor

| PIR Pin | Arduino Pin |
| ------- | ----------- |
| VCC     | 5V          |
| OUT     | D2          |
| GND     | GND         |

### Street Light LED

| Component       | Arduino Pin               |
| --------------- | ------------------------- |
| LED Anode (+)   | D9                        |
| LED Cathode (-) | GND through 220Ω resistor |

## Working Principle

The system operates in three modes:

### 1. Daytime Mode

When sufficient ambient light is detected by the LDR, the street light remains OFF.

```text
Condition:
LDR Value > Threshold
```

Output:

* Street light OFF

---

### 2. Night Mode (No Motion)

When it is dark and no motion is detected, the LED glows at reduced brightness using PWM.

Output:

* Street light DIM (~30% brightness)

---

### 3. Night Mode (Motion Detected)

When motion is detected during nighttime, the LED switches to full brightness.

Output:

* Street light at 100% brightness

## PWM Brightness Levels

| Condition         | PWM Value | Brightness      |
| ----------------- | --------- | --------------- |
| Daytime           | 0         | OFF             |
| Night + No Motion | 80        | Dim             |
| Night + Motion    | 255       | Full Brightness |

## Serial Monitor Output Example

```text
LDR Value: 850 Motion: 0
DAYTIME -> LIGHT OFF

LDR Value: 320 Motion: 0
NIGHT + NO MOTION -> DIM MODE

LDR Value: 280 Motion: 1
NIGHT + MOTION -> FULL BRIGHTNESS
```

